{
  "_comment": "Test fixtures for Checkpoint 2 (Hand Analysis Layer). Each pose provides a 21-landmark list with (x, y, z) tuples in normalized MediaPipe coordinate space (0..1). Coordinates are deterministic synthetic values designed to exercise the geometric primitives in gesture_utils.py.\n\nPose conventions (per MediaPipe Hands landmark layout):\n  WRIST = 0\n  THUMB_CMC=1, THUMB_MCP=2, THUMB_IP=3, THUMB_TIP=4\n  INDEX_MCP=5, INDEX_PIP=6, INDEX_DIP=7, INDEX_TIP=8\n  MIDDLE_MCP=9, MIDDLE_PIP=10, MIDDLE_DIP=11, MIDDLE_TIP=12\n  RING_MCP=13, RING_PIP=14, RING_DIP=15, RING_TIP=16\n  PINKY_MCP=17, PINKY_PIP=18, PINKY_DIP=19, PINKY_TIP=20\n\nGeometry:\n  - WRIST at y=0.55\n  - Extended fingers: PIP/DIP/TIP stack straight above MCP (lower y)\n  - Curled fingers: PIP forward (y decreases), TIP bent back inward (toward wrist y, x increases toward palm center)\n  - The PIP angle is the critical measurement for finger-state classification:\n      ~180 deg = straight (EXTENDED)\n      ~80 deg = sharply bent (CURLED)\n\nEach pose targets a specific gesture-recognizer outcome:\n  open_palm_* -> all five fingers EXTENDED (PIP angle >= 160 deg)\n  fist_right -> all four non-thumb fingers CURLED (PIP angle < 130 deg)\n  pinch_right -> thumb tip close to index tip (normalized distance < 0.35)\n  peace_sign_right -> index + middle extended, ring + pinky curled\n  three_fingers_right -> index + middle + ring extended, pinky curled\n  thumbs_up_right -> only thumb extended (pointing up)\n  ok_sign_right -> thumb-index contact AND middle + ring + pinky extended\n",

